{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]When the years show in our faces
[G7]From the thoughtless hand of time
[C]And our youth is just a memory to revive
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
We'll spend many happy hours
[F]Thumbing through the past desires
[C]And we'll bring [F]each tender [C]memory [G7]back to [C]life
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[F]For every day we live we add a [C]memory
[G7]And we store it in the corner of our minds
[F]And when life's fire is just a dying [C]ember
[F]We'll bring [C]each tender [G7]memory back to [C]life
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
When we know our days are numbered
[G7]That we live on borrowed time
[C]Our hands will search the darkness to entwine
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
